Question: What is the marginal data likelihood?

Answer: The marginal data likelihood is:

\begin{equation}
\begin{aligned}
\log p(x) &= \log p(x|y) \\
&= \log p(y|x) \\
&= \log p(y) \\
&= \log p(y|x) \\
&= \log p(x)
\end{aligned}
\end{equation}

